Fort.<br>
<br>
Those are the easy camps in Chardok. The camps you do when you don't have enough people.<br>
<br>
I just spent all of last night in the Graveyard.<br>
<br>
Yes, it's deep in there. That's what a dungeon crawl is for.<br>
<br>
But Reanimated Beserkers and Imperial Constructs were all even cons at level 55.<br>
<br>
The XP was amazing. I hadn't seen XP movement like THAT since I was level 40 something.<br>
<br>
The mobs on the way TO the graveyard (including your standard pits pulls from Captain's room and the Bridge) are all high 40s to mid 50s mobs.<br>
<br>
They're all very good XP, just like they used to be.<br>
<br>
Yeah, it's hard. Yeah, it's not something you find a &quot;pickup group&quot; for.<br>
<br>
I didn't say that.<br>
<br>
I just wanted to add CHARDOK to the list of places that you can go to and take advantage of the change in XPing.<br>
<br>
A good Chardok grouping always did the kick the crap out of your standard Seb or Velk's grouping for both fun and XP.<br>
<br>
If you don't want to go to Chardok you don't have to. All I'm saying is, it's THERE. Right up there with Akheva Ruins and Sssra Temple as a place to find challenging XP mobs in this post patch era. But unlike those Luclin deathtraps, Chardok is a bit less stressful (at least for me).<br>
